WEBVTT

00:02.175 --> 00:05.011
What's my favorite way to relax?

00:05.094 --> 00:09.348
Throw on my wireless headphones
and disappear into the Nature Channel.

00:09.473 --> 00:13.019
33 [ Instrumental ] [ Man ] The
young flatback turtle searches for food...

00:13.102 --> 00:14.979
<i>on the ocean floor.</i>

00:15.104 --> 00:17.749
<i>This flatback, however— [ Phil]
The fascinating thing about nature...</i>

00:17.773 --> 00:19.400
<i>is how, in the blink of an eye,</i>

00:19.483 --> 00:22.862
<i>it can go from a scene
of total tranquil beauty...</i>

00:22.945 --> 00:25.198
<i>to raw, primal violence.</i>

00:25.281 --> 00:28.117
Can you seriously not hear
me with those things on?

00:28.201 --> 00:31.162
It's noise-canceling technology.
Give it a spin. It's got...

00:31.245 --> 00:34.165
- Sweetie, focus, now.
- Mom, why are you freaking out
on everyone?

00:34.248 --> 00:37.335
Because you are acting
very irresponsibly— all of you.

00:37.418 --> 00:40.564
Listen, honey. Luke has a giant project due
tomorrow for school that he hasn't even started,

00:40.588 --> 00:43.883
and Haley just informed me she needs
40 cupcakes for her school fund—raiser,

00:43.966 --> 00:45.885
<i>also due tomorrow.</i>

00:45.968 --> 00:49.972
I'd like to point out I completed all my
assignments on my own and on time.

00:50.056 --> 00:52.183
[ Together]
Not now, Alex.

00:52.266 --> 00:55.561
I will take the cupcakes. You do
the project. It's on Vincent van Gogh.

00:55.686 --> 00:58.481
Done! I need you to really
stay on him. Keep him focused.

00:58.564 --> 01:01.525
All right. I'm actually gonna
take a different approach, but...

01:01.609 --> 01:03.527
Actually gonna insist
that you don't.

01:03.611 --> 01:06.072
Claire, I know you've got
your methods, but so do I.

01:06.155 --> 01:08.449
And I'm sorry,
but I'm not a micromanager.

01:08.532 --> 01:12.578
Trust me, I can provide Luke with
the tools and guidance he needs...

01:12.662 --> 01:15.081
without, uh, smothering him.

01:15.206 --> 01:18.084
You think I smother our child?
It's not your fault, honey.

01:18.167 --> 01:20.086
“Mother” is part of the word.

01:20.169 --> 01:22.505
You never hear of anyone
being “sfathered” to death.

01:22.588 --> 01:26.050
<i>I know what Luke's problem is.
He's got A.D. H. D.</i>

01:26.175 --> 01:28.052
[ Claire ] No. No, I don't!

01:28.177 --> 01:32.515
What is it? I'd tell you, but you'd
wander off before I got to the “.H”

01:32.598 --> 01:35.810
Just promise me that you will
stay on him until this project is done.

01:35.893 --> 01:38.729
I will, but you might have a
little more confidence in him.

01:38.813 --> 01:43.609
<i>Web! Web!
No one can hear me now.</i>

01:43.693 --> 01:46.279
Whoo!

01:46.362 --> 01:49.156
Everybody is stupid except me.

01:49.240 --> 01:52.118
<i>Ha, ha, ha.
I am funny.</i>

01:53.327 --> 01:55.413
<i>([ Man ] J“ Hey, hey)</i>

01:55.496 --> 01:59.583
<i>(Y Hey, hey Hey, hey)</i>

01:59.667 --> 02:02.586
<i>Y Hey, hey Heyw</i>

02:05.089 --> 02:07.967
Is this the cutest thing
I've ever seen?

02:08.050 --> 02:11.512
You out here on the curb with your
little telescope, waiting for your dad.

02:11.595 --> 02:13.264
It's not cute.
It's-It's science.

02:13.347 --> 02:16.767
Tonight is the magnificent
Lyrid meteor shower.

02:16.892 --> 02:19.162
It's where the planet Geek
passes through the Nerdy Way. It...

02:19.186 --> 02:21.105
Oh, you know I think it's sweet.

02:21.188 --> 02:24.859
Every couple years, Mitchell and his father go
out and enjoy one of these showers together.

02:24.942 --> 02:27.445
Oh, I— I wouldn't necessarily
put it that way.

02:27.528 --> 02:31.782
I mean, yes, me and my father enjoy it, because
we don't share a lot of the same interests.

02:31.866 --> 02:35.661
Like, um, I-I never went
to sports games with him.

02:35.745 --> 02:38.247
Probably because you
call 'em “sports games.”

02:39.373 --> 02:42.835
Just lose the “sports.”
Just— Just games.

02:42.960 --> 02:45.546
Oh, here comes your
shower partner. Stop it.

02:45.671 --> 02:48.632
I'm kidding. Have fun with your
dad, okay? All right. See you later.

02:48.758 --> 02:51.344
Don't worry about me.
I'm not.

02:51.427 --> 02:54.305
I'm just saying, if you were.

02:54.388 --> 02:58.267
- Shotgun, sucka!
<i>- [Jay Laughing]</i>

03:01.354 --> 03:03.707
[ Cameron ] Make sure your
seat is exactly the way you want it,

03:03.731 --> 03:06.400
and feel free to play with any
of these controls up here.

03:06.484 --> 03:10.905
I have no idea what they do.
But I want ml car to be su car.

03:10.988 --> 03:14.200
Cameron, are you okay?
You seem nervous.

03:14.283 --> 03:16.619
Uh, nervous?
No. I'm not nervous.

03:18.996 --> 03:20.748
I was nervous.

03:20.831 --> 03:22.792
I mean, when Mitchell
made plans with his father,

03:22.875 --> 03:25.044
I figured, why not spend
the evening with Gloria?

03:25.127 --> 03:27.421
I've always wanted to
be good friends with her.

03:27.505 --> 03:29.173
On paper, we should
be good friends.

03:29.256 --> 03:31.801
Look at us.
One spicy, curvy diva...

03:31.884 --> 03:34.095
And Gloria.

03:34.178 --> 03:37.264
The problem is, I had a little minor
setback that we had to overcome...

03:37.348 --> 03:38.974
from a couple weeks ago.

03:39.100 --> 03:41.453
[ Phil, Jay Chattering] I cannot stand
hanging out with his Ivy League friends.

03:41.477 --> 03:43.038
Oh, they're the worst.
They're not that bad.

03:43.062 --> 03:44.582
They are the worst!
Are you kidding me?

03:44.647 --> 03:47.441
Debbie can't go two minutes without
talking about Columbia University.

03:47.566 --> 03:50.403
And the little guy with the
lazy eye from Harvard. Brown.

03:50.486 --> 03:53.489
Whatever. Honestly, I wish that tart
would go back to Columbia...

03:53.572 --> 03:55.452
and take her weird
little Brown friend with her.

03:55.533 --> 03:57.201
[ Chuckles ]
[Chattering Stops]

03:59.829 --> 04:01.664
[ Mouthing Words]

04:03.582 --> 04:05.584
Cam, you need to relax.
You explained.

04:05.668 --> 04:07.628
Not very well.

04:07.711 --> 04:10.464
You know how awkward I get
when things get awkward.

04:10.548 --> 04:14.677
So when I said “Brown people,” I wasn't
talking about your, uh, brown people.

04:14.760 --> 04:18.013
I was talking about people
who go to a university.

04:18.097 --> 04:20.015
Um, not your people.

04:20.099 --> 04:23.185
N-Not that your people
couldn't go to college.

04:23.269 --> 04:26.397
Okay, now I'm hearing myself
say “your people” a lot, so...

04:26.480 --> 04:29.108
[ Chokes ]

04:29.191 --> 04:32.111
Um, just very excited
because this is, um...

04:32.194 --> 04:35.322
You know, this is our first night
out together, so it's our little date.

04:35.406 --> 04:37.324
Where are we going?

04:37.408 --> 04:39.577
Make sure your seat belt
is securely fastened...

04:39.660 --> 04:41.787
and your tray tables are
in the upright position...

04:41.871 --> 04:44.081
because I got us into Palaiseau!

04:44.206 --> 04:46.125
Ah! Fancy!
I know.

04:46.208 --> 04:48.127
It's normally a four-week wait,

04:48.210 --> 04:51.422
but the maTtre d' is an old Pilates
brother of mine, so just one phone call.

04:51.505 --> 04:53.174
Okay.

04:53.299 --> 04:56.802
Palaiseau!
[ Chuckles ]

04:56.886 --> 05:01.307
Ay, Cameron, you know what? I don't know
if I'm in the mood for something so fancy.

05:01.390 --> 05:04.560
Can we just go somewhere,
like, more simple?

05:04.643 --> 05:07.021
Oh, uh, yes.
Yes, of course.

05:07.104 --> 05:10.524
We can— What were—
What did you have in mind?

05:11.567 --> 05:13.486
I don't know.

05:13.569 --> 05:16.655
How 'bout a little Latin place
that I always used to go?

05:16.780 --> 05:18.699
That sounds fantastic.
Okay.

05:18.782 --> 05:20.784
I would love to see
how your people eat.

05:20.868 --> 05:23.120
“Your people”?

05:23.204 --> 05:25.289
What is wrong with me?

05:25.539 --> 05:28.959
Okay. It's egg-crackin' time. Now, I
find the key to cracking an egg properly...

05:29.043 --> 05:31.253
Mom, I'm not a child.
I can do it.

05:31.378 --> 05:33.964
Okay. Okay.
Okay.

05:34.048 --> 05:37.843
My <i>mom's</i> not dumb. You can't
just ask her to do something for you.

05:37.927 --> 05:41.931
You have to very carefully
put the cheese in the trap.

05:44.558 --> 05:46.560
Oh. Oops. I got
a little shell in the bowl.

05:46.644 --> 05:50.648
- When that happens, I find
that I like to... not do that.
- I got it. It's okay.

05:50.773 --> 05:54.109
Oh, that's— that's really gross.
Okay. I'm gonna— I'll do this.

05:54.193 --> 05:56.362
You just mop up.

05:56.445 --> 05:58.405
And snap.

05:58.489 --> 06:00.616
Is it bad that I feel sorry for her?

06:00.699 --> 06:04.119
So how do I start?
What do you think?

06:04.203 --> 06:06.872
I don't know. Mom usually
tells me what to do.

06:06.956 --> 06:10.209
Join the club.
I'm kidding. I love your mom.

06:10.292 --> 06:13.921
We are going to try
a new approach this time.

06:14.004 --> 06:17.550
<i>Now, your goal is to create a display
about the life and art of van Gog/7, night?</i>

06:17.675 --> 06:21.220
Yeah. <i>Okay. You got your
poster board right here.</i>

06:21.303 --> 06:25.266
So, pretend you're telling
the story of his life...

06:25.349 --> 06:27.351
to someone who has
never heard of him.

06:27.434 --> 06:30.771
What do you put on that board?

06:30.854 --> 06:33.857
I see the wheels spinning.
A spark of crea...

06:33.983 --> 06:36.819
How do they get the lead in
pencils? Let's try to stay on topic.

06:36.902 --> 06:42.408
Hey, Jay. Look who thinks Mercury is
the densest planet in the solar system.

06:42.491 --> 06:45.202
I take it from your mocking
tone that I am incorrect.

06:45.286 --> 06:47.204
Densest planet is Earth.

06:47.288 --> 06:50.082
Which makes you the densest
guy on the densest planet.

06:50.165 --> 06:52.418
Zing!
Fine.

06:52.501 --> 06:54.837
You sure Mitchell
won't mind me tagging along?

06:54.920 --> 06:57.923
Are you kidding? He loves
ya. What are you worried about?

06:58.007 --> 07:01.594
I've never had a brother before.
We never really hung out that much.

07:01.677 --> 07:03.762
Kiddo, you are
overthinking this.

07:03.846 --> 07:05.889
I just don't wanna
say the wrong thing.

07:05.973 --> 07:08.267
You can't. That's the
beauty of having a brother.

07:08.350 --> 07:10.686
Me and my brother were
zinging each other all the time.

07:10.769 --> 07:14.273
You know, like, “What's going on,
fat boy?” “Nothing much, jackass.”

07:14.356 --> 07:16.317
You know, things of that nature.

07:16.400 --> 07:19.194
It's— It's how brothers
express love.

07:19.278 --> 07:21.196
Hmm.

07:23.741 --> 07:26.744
- Shotgun, sucka!
<i>- [Jay Laughing]</i>

07:26.827 --> 07:29.204
Yeah. That's good.

07:29.288 --> 07:31.999
I'm gonna see the sights.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.628
Not if they see you first!

07:35.711 --> 07:38.213
Kind of missed
with that one, kid.

07:39.340 --> 07:41.258
All right.

07:41.342 --> 07:44.428
This is all you
need to know right here.

07:44.511 --> 07:47.616
Apparently, the pencil's in two pieces,
and they glue 'em together on the lead.

07:47.640 --> 07:50.476
What if we put all the stuff
about his life on this side...

07:50.559 --> 07:53.062
and all the stuff about
his paintings on this side?

07:53.145 --> 07:55.022
Luke, buddy, that's fantastic!

07:55.105 --> 07:57.316
And the best part is, you
came up with that by yourself.

07:57.399 --> 07:58.609
[ Rattling ]

07:58.692 --> 08:01.987
All it took was a little
bit of focus and, uh...

08:02.071 --> 08:05.616
This thing is really loose.
I'm gonna go grab a screwdriver.

08:05.699 --> 08:08.994
But you run with this. On
your mark, get set, van Gogh.

08:09.078 --> 08:10.996
<i>[Door Opens ]</i>
Hey, Dad.

08:11.080 --> 08:14.249
He kind of looks like Uncle Mitchell,
if Uncle Mitchell were insane.

08:14.333 --> 08:16.502
- [ Chuckles]
<i>- [Door Closes ]</i>

08:16.585 --> 08:19.463
<i>[ Screaming ]
I got sprayed by a skunk!</i>

08:19.588 --> 08:22.591
Oh! [Whimpering ] Oh, you stink!

08:22.675 --> 08:25.010
And not just at astronomy!
Blammo!

08:25.135 --> 08:27.096
[ Groans ]
What is happening?

08:30.140 --> 08:32.309
<i>([ Woman] LQué past)?</i>

08:33.477 --> 08:35.396
I love this place.

08:35.479 --> 08:37.856
I was a little bit worried
because it's not exactly...

08:37.981 --> 08:41.026
I... love... this place.
[Chuckles]

08:41.110 --> 08:43.278
I... was... nervous.

08:43.362 --> 08:45.989
I mean, there was a lot of
different food on the menu,

08:46.073 --> 08:48.033
and on the floor,
and on the wall.

08:48.117 --> 08:50.744
Uh— Are we— Are we sure we're
not exaggerating just a little bit?

08:50.828 --> 08:52.496
Were you there, Mitchell?

08:52.579 --> 08:55.833
Because I think I would have recognized
the only other white or gay person.

08:55.916 --> 08:59.503
I'd already offended Gloria once.
Not gonna do it again.

08:59.586 --> 09:02.089
Hola. ¢Cémo esté?
