09:12.099 --> 09:14.685
No, no, no. You should
have the chicken enchiladas.

09:14.810 --> 09:17.813
Mm-hmm.
No, I'll have the carnitas diablos.

09:17.896 --> 09:19.940
- These are not for you.
- Excuse me?

09:20.023 --> 09:23.152
- They're too spicy. Miss Gloria's used to it.
- Yeah, he's right.

09:23.235 --> 09:27.406
I can spice you under the
table any day there, sweet thing.

09:27.489 --> 09:30.909
<i>Dos carnitas diablos, por favor.</i>

09:30.993 --> 09:32.578
Okay.

09:32.703 --> 09:34.538
Okay.
[Giggling ]

09:34.621 --> 09:36.749
[ Clears Throat]

09:36.832 --> 09:40.419
- Mitchell!
- Of course. What was I thinking?

09:40.502 --> 09:43.005
[Sighs] Dad, can we— can
we just go home, please?

09:43.088 --> 09:47.217
You've got to air out first before I let you
in that car. I'll never get the stink out.

09:47.301 --> 09:49.720
<i>Hey, Jay, is that Venus?</i>

09:49.803 --> 09:52.598
'Cause I can smell the clouds
of pure sulfuric acid from here.

09:52.681 --> 09:56.101
- Slam!
- Okay. I-I'd really like
to go home now.

09:56.226 --> 09:58.896
We'll miss the meteor shower.
The trouble is your clothes.

09:58.979 --> 10:01.982
Just take them off. I think
there's a blanket in the trunk.

10:02.065 --> 10:04.419
You sure, Dad? You're not
worried I might stink up the blanket?

10:04.443 --> 10:06.361
Don't worry about it.

10:06.445 --> 10:10.115
We just use it to cover up the seat for when
Manny's all sweaty after his tango class.

10:10.199 --> 10:12.743
If you don't sweat,
you're not doing it right.

10:17.122 --> 10:18.874
[Laughing]

10:18.957 --> 10:21.627
He was one of the best
boyfriends I ever had.

10:21.752 --> 10:24.213
But he was gay.
Yeah.

10:24.338 --> 10:26.465
I figured that out after
the first month— [ Coughs ]

10:26.548 --> 10:28.902
and I stayed for a whole year
because the haircuts were fantastic!

10:28.926 --> 10:31.887
[ Laughing, Crying]
It's funny, huh?

10:32.012 --> 10:34.640
[ Hysterical Laughing ]
Cameron, that one is not that funny.

10:34.765 --> 10:36.183
Are you okay?
I'm fine.

10:36.308 --> 10:38.560
Are you sure?
I love this place.

10:38.685 --> 10:41.355
[ Coughing ] But your
head is running water.

10:41.438 --> 10:43.232
No, I don't think it is.

10:43.315 --> 10:46.401
I told you it was too spicy
for you. Look at your shirt.

10:46.527 --> 10:49.029
I just need to get a bit of a
drink of something. No, no, no!

10:49.154 --> 10:52.074
Cameron, the water makes it so
worse. No! Excuse me. Excuse me.

10:53.408 --> 10:55.661
Oh, you're right.
That does make it worse.

10:55.744 --> 10:57.996
Oh— I feel like I ate the sun!

10:58.080 --> 11:03.043
And that is the secret to no
lumps. See? It's kind of fun.

11:03.126 --> 11:05.003
- You make it fun, Mom.
- Mmm.

11:05.087 --> 11:07.840
Listen to these symptoms of A.D.H.D.
and tell me it's not Luke.

11:07.965 --> 11:11.552
Alex! “Easily distracted
by irrelevant stimuli.”

11:14.763 --> 11:16.682
<i>[ Electrical Buzzing ]</i>

11:21.270 --> 11:25.566
<i>“Often impulsively abandons
one task for another.”</i>

11:31.572 --> 11:33.490
That's where I left those.

11:33.574 --> 11:36.451
“A tendency to act
without regard to consequences,

11:36.535 --> 11:40.163
often at the expense
of personal safety.”

11:48.463 --> 11:51.008
[Grunts]

11:57.556 --> 12:01.476
- “Ha <i>v/ng accidents more oflen</i> ”— - I
think that's enough, Alex. <i>We've</i> got it.

12:16.325 --> 12:19.328
Oh, no. No!

12:19.411 --> 12:21.955
<i>[ Clattering ]</i>

12:22.039 --> 12:23.081
[ Exhales]

12:23.165 --> 12:25.500
Phil. Phil!
Honey, are you okay?

12:25.584 --> 12:29.296
Yeah. Remember those
sunglasses I couldn't find?

12:29.379 --> 12:31.632
Bingo!
[ Chuckles ]

12:31.715 --> 12:34.509
I asked you to do one thing—
Stay on top of Luke.

12:34.593 --> 12:37.596
For your information, your son is
hard at work on an awesome van Gogh...

12:37.679 --> 12:39.598
Gotta fix that— masterpiece.

12:39.681 --> 12:41.934
Wait'II you see.
You're gonna be so surprised.

12:42.017 --> 12:45.729
Oh, God, honey. I want nothing
more than to be surprised, really.

12:48.732 --> 12:51.026
Oh.

12:51.109 --> 12:53.111
I'm not surprised.

12:55.405 --> 12:58.867
Okay, that's it. I don't want to hear anything
about your new method of doing things.

12:58.951 --> 13:02.162
There's one thing that works with these
kids, and that is staying on top of them,

13:02.245 --> 13:06.667
which, thanks to you, my friend,
I will now be able to do all night long.

13:14.299 --> 13:17.386
- Not happy, dude. You're supposed to be working.
- I am working.

13:17.469 --> 13:19.805
- Mr. Potato Head, really?
- I know what you think, but...

13:19.888 --> 13:22.474
No, I don't wanna hear it. I'm
going down to clean up the garage,

13:22.557 --> 13:26.228
then I'm coming back and I'm gonna stand
over you until this thing is done, okay?

13:33.735 --> 13:35.570
Breathe. Breathing only
makes the fire spread.

13:35.654 --> 13:37.322
<i>Okay. Then drink this milk.</i>

13:37.406 --> 13:41.284
Ay, Cam. Why did you
have to order that spicy dish?

13:41.368 --> 13:43.495
Because I'm, um, a big idiot...

13:43.578 --> 13:47.290
and I wanted to have this awesome
night between the two of us...

13:47.374 --> 13:51.920
where we end up best friends,
uh, having lunch, buying shoes.

13:52.004 --> 13:56.008
Okay! Let's go have lunch,
let's go buy shoes.

13:56.133 --> 13:59.011
Really?
Yeah. Why are you so surprised?

13:59.094 --> 14:03.140
Well, I don't know. I guess I just
always feel like I blow it with you...

14:03.223 --> 14:05.350
whether it's
the Columbian comment...

14:05.434 --> 14:07.394
or picking the wrong restaurant.

14:07.477 --> 14:11.064
The restaurant
had nothing to do with you.

14:11.148 --> 14:14.151
I was just not in the mood
to go anywhere that fancy...

14:14.234 --> 14:17.362
after the stupid thing
I did this morning.

14:17.446 --> 14:19.906
What did you do?

14:20.032 --> 14:22.993
I bought a dress.
You monster.

14:23.076 --> 14:26.038
Ay. It was a very expensive
dress that I don't need.

14:26.121 --> 14:28.373
I felt so stupid
that when I got home,

14:28.457 --> 14:30.625
I couldn't even bring it
inside the house.

14:30.751 --> 14:32.878
I left it in the car.
I totally get it.

14:32.961 --> 14:34.880
I have a legendary hat story.

14:34.963 --> 14:37.090
I'll bet you look fabulous
in that dress.

14:37.215 --> 14:40.343
Yes, but anyone would look
fabulous in that dress. [ Chuckling ]

14:40.469 --> 14:44.097
You find that blanket?
No.

14:44.181 --> 14:46.600
This was all I could find.
Shut up!

14:46.683 --> 14:49.394
- Really shows off your shape.
- Okay.

14:49.478 --> 14:51.855
Spin around, cupcake.
Let's see the caboose!

14:51.938 --> 14:56.026
<i>You get fries with that
shake? [ Wheezing Laugh]</i>

14:56.151 --> 14:58.945
Was that too far?
There's a line, Jay.

14:59.029 --> 15:01.323
I better go mop this up.

15:02.324 --> 15:04.785
Oh, come on.
Where's the...

15:04.868 --> 15:07.579
[ Clears Throat]

15:07.662 --> 15:11.333
I'm sorry if things got a
little out of hand back there,

15:11.416 --> 15:13.418
but in our defense, look at you.

15:13.502 --> 15:15.462
[ Chuckling ]
I mean, smell you.

15:15.545 --> 15:17.631
[Mock Laughing ]
This is a fantastic apology.

15:17.714 --> 15:20.967
Oh, don't be too hard on
the kid. I was egging him on.

15:22.344 --> 15:25.472
You're gonna be mad,
be mad at me. Done!

15:25.555 --> 15:28.016
I was just happy to see him
laugh a little bit.

15:28.100 --> 15:30.102
You know, he's had
kind of a tough week.

15:30.185 --> 15:34.439
I got sprayed by a skunk, and I'm wearing
a dress that makes my hips look huge.

15:34.523 --> 15:37.234
I know he doesn't want me
to talk about it,

15:37.317 --> 15:40.195
but he didn't get invited
to this big party.

15:40.278 --> 15:43.281
Some kids he thought were
his friends think he's weird.

15:44.950 --> 15:47.577
Now, you know me on this.
I'm no— I'm no good at it.

15:47.702 --> 15:50.997
You know, I— I never know
what to say. That's true.

15:51.081 --> 15:54.376
But maybe I raised a kid
who would know what to say.

15:56.211 --> 15:58.171
That's the only reason
I invited him along...

15:58.255 --> 16:01.716
You know, because this astronomy
stuff, that's— that's our thing.

16:01.800 --> 16:03.718
[ Chuckles ]

16:05.011 --> 16:06.930
Yeah.
No, I'll talk to him.

16:07.013 --> 16:09.141
You know, you don't look
that ridiculous.

16:09.266 --> 16:11.434
Now, you actually
got the legs for it. Dad.

16:11.560 --> 16:14.146
No, I'm just saying, if you
were that type of a gay— Dad!

16:14.229 --> 16:16.231
You'd probably do
all right for yourself.

16:16.314 --> 16:18.233
<i>Come on!</i>

16:19.693 --> 16:22.320
You know, I always had a sense
it was dangerous down here,

16:22.404 --> 16:24.948
but I guess it's actually
kind of charming, isn't it?

16:25.073 --> 16:27.951
<i>No,</i> it's <i>not</i> safe <i>at</i> all.
<i>[ Sire/7 Wailing In Distance ]</i>

16:28.076 --> 16:30.996
I used to live down
here, you know. What?

16:31.079 --> 16:33.874
Yeah, that's why I come
down here. Look there.

16:33.957 --> 16:35.876
<i>That was my old apartment.</i>

16:35.959 --> 16:38.753
After I left Javier,
that's all I could afford.

16:38.879 --> 16:40.797
It's still part of me.
Mmm.

16:40.881 --> 16:44.593
You have to remember those things,
like you when you go to your farm.

16:44.676 --> 16:46.928
You remember that?
I told you that a year ago.

16:47.012 --> 16:50.473
Of course I do. You're
my friend, you big idiot.

16:50.557 --> 16:54.352
[ Laughing ] You know, this
part of town might be very rough,

16:54.436 --> 16:57.272
but the people here,
Cameron— the best.

16:59.149 --> 17:01.401
<i>I'm pretty sure I had wheels
when I parked here.</i>

17:01.484 --> 17:03.445
<i>IAyayay-f Who did</i> this?

17:03.570 --> 17:06.448
No, it's okay, Gloria. [
Shouting ] Who did this?

17:06.573 --> 17:10.368
You coward son of bitches! It's
okay, everybody! I'm— I'm insured!

17:10.452 --> 17:15.165
What? What? You scared? You
scared to show your face, little girl?

17:15.290 --> 17:17.959
No, it's all right, everybody!
Cameron, wait in the car!

17:18.084 --> 17:20.212
Gloria, I think it's drivable.
<i>Cameron!</i>

17:20.295 --> 17:21.713
<i>Gloria!</i>

17:23.757 --> 17:27.427
Just so you know, I'm going back up to Luke's
room, and I'm not leaving until he's finished.

17:27.552 --> 17:31.431
Thank you. And I'm really sorry for
not underestimating Luke enough.

17:31.514 --> 17:33.975
Well, that means a lot to me.

17:34.059 --> 17:36.561
The hardest part is, he kinda
takes after me with all this.

17:36.686 --> 17:38.980
Hmm. Like my lack
of focus and your...

17:39.105 --> 17:41.107
My what?
I just love you.

17:46.112 --> 17:48.031
<i>I did it. [Phil] Hey.</i>

17:48.114 --> 17:49.991
Oh, my God.

17:50.075 --> 17:53.536
- Do you like it?
- I-I— I love it.

17:53.662 --> 17:55.664
Did you do this?
All him.

17:55.747 --> 17:59.251
I used Mr. Potato Head ears
because van Gogh cut his ear off.

17:59.334 --> 18:02.837
And there's money because his paintings
sell for, like, a bajillion dollars,

18:02.921 --> 18:05.548
<i>which is sad
because he died broke.</i>

18:05.632 --> 18:07.759
Yes. That...

18:07.884 --> 18:10.095
[Whispers ] You were
right. Don't apologize.

18:10.220 --> 18:13.181
I'm not apologizing.
Apology accepted.

18:13.265 --> 18:15.976
<i>Luke, I-I really couldn't
be more proud of you,</i>

18:16.059 --> 18:18.520
and I am so sorry I didn't
give you more credit.

18:18.645 --> 18:20.647
Thanks. <i>[ Phil]
Way to go, buddy.</i>

18:22.691 --> 18:25.443
[Clicks Tongue]
Gotta go finish the cupcakes.

18:25.527 --> 18:28.154
[Chuckling]
No. She didn't.

18:28.238 --> 18:30.865
- Sweetie, can you hand me those?
- Uh-huh.

18:30.949 --> 18:33.493
Yeah, I can talk.

18:33.576 --> 18:34.911
What are you doing?

18:34.995 --> 18:38.039
I showed you how to make 'em,
and now you can do it yourself.

18:39.541 --> 18:41.167
Come on, guys. Let's go.

18:42.210 --> 18:45.630
Well, good, because
I really wanted to.

18:45.714 --> 18:48.591
Okay. I'm setting
the oven to 700!

18:48.675 --> 18:52.304
I'm putting, uh— I'm putting
the eggs in the bowl!

18:52.387 --> 18:54.931
Oh, I got some shells
in 'em! Uh-oh!

18:55.015 --> 18:58.893
Are you serious?
[ Exhales]

19:02.439 --> 19:04.482
Hey. Hey.
Hey, Mitchell.

19:04.566 --> 19:06.901
So, I know you'd never, um...

19:08.820 --> 19:12.115
I know you'd never, never believe this
by looking at me right now,

19:12.198 --> 19:15.035
but, um, I used to
get picked on at school too.

19:15.118 --> 19:17.829
80 Jay told you?
Yeah.

19:17.912 --> 19:20.457
Yeah, they would, um—
They'd call me weird.

19:20.540 --> 19:23.084
I was weird.
Uh, fun weird.

19:23.168 --> 19:25.712
But I— This is the funny thing
about growing up.

19:25.795 --> 19:28.214
For years and years,
everybody's desperately afraid...

19:28.298 --> 19:31.217
to be different,
you know, in any way.

19:31.301 --> 19:34.596
And then, suddenly,
almost overnight,

19:34.679 --> 19:37.223
everybody wants to be different,

19:37.307 --> 19:41.061
and that is where we win.

19:41.186 --> 19:44.230
I'm sort of counting on that.
Yeah.

19:44.356 --> 19:46.733
I'm sorry I was picking on
you too much. Ah, that's...

19:46.858 --> 19:49.277
Jay said that's what
brothers do. [ Chuckles ]

19:49.361 --> 19:52.447
Well, we don't have to listen to him.
Brothers do that too.

19:52.530 --> 19:54.991
<i>Okay, ladies.
Finish up your tea party.</i>

19:55.075 --> 19:56.576
You're missing the show.

19:56.659 --> 19:59.371
Can't believe I was fighting
over this guy, huh?

19:59.496 --> 20:02.248
Check it out. Check it out.
Oh. Whoa.

20:03.249 --> 20:05.168
Wow.
Awesome!

20:09.631 --> 20:11.841
<i>[Luke] Why did he
paint The</i> Starry Night?

20:13.426 --> 20:17.514
<i>Maybe because the sky is beautiful,
and everybody likes looking at it,</i>

20:19.724 --> 20:24.187
<i>and it reminds us that something's
up there watching over all of us—</i>

20:24.270 --> 20:28.024
Aliens, who could be here
in a second...

20:28.108 --> 20:30.110
<i>to liquefi/ us
and use us as fuel.</i>

20:30.193 --> 20:32.779
So wake up, people.
We're next.

20:32.862 --> 20:34.781
Mom!

20:34.864 --> 20:36.825
You better get down here!

20:42.288 --> 20:43.790
Mmm!
Oh, my God.

20:43.915 --> 20:46.418
Wow! Delicious!
<i>Uh-huh.</i>

20:46.501 --> 20:49.421
- I am so proud.
- Oh! Thanks, Mom. I'm just gonna wrap these up.

20:49.504 --> 20:52.024
No. You know what, sweetie? You're
gonna be late for school. Just go.

20:52.048 --> 20:53.925
- I'll bring 'em by later.
- Are you sure?

20:54.050 --> 20:56.094
Yeah! Get out of here,
Betty Crocker. Okay.

20:56.177 --> 20:58.096
I'm so proud of you!

20:58.179 --> 21:00.098
[Gagging, Spits]

21:00.181 --> 21:02.183
Do we still have the number
for Poison Control?

21:02.267 --> 21:04.561
I love you, Claire.
I'll always love you!

21:04.644 --> 21:06.438
My mouth is asleep,
like at the dentist.

21:06.521 --> 21:08.523
Get over here, buddy.

21:09.983 --> 21:12.026
[ Grunts]
[Whimpers]

21:12.110 --> 21:14.028
<i>[ Luke Grunts]</i>

21:16.906 --> 21:17.907
ENGLISH <i>—</i> US - PSDH
